            <p permid="faz">
              First find the slope through our points:
              <m>\left(-3,\frac{3}{4}\right)</m> and <m>\left(-6,-\frac{17}{4}\right)</m>.
              For this problem,
              we choose to do all of our algebra with improper fractions as it often simplifies the process.
              <md permid="wnf">
                <mrow>m\amp=\frac{y_2-y_1}{x_2-x_1}</mrow>
                <mrow>\amp=\frac{\substitute{-\frac{17}{4}}-\substitute{\frac{3}{4}}}{\substitute{-6}-\substitute{(-3)}}</mrow>
                <mrow>\amp=\frac{\frac{-20}{4}}{-3}</mrow>
