                <mrow>\amp=\frac{5}{3}</mrow>
              </md>
            </p>

            <p permid="LhI">
              So far we have <m>y=\frac{5}{3}x+b</m>.
              Now we need to solve for <m>b</m> since neither of the points given were the vertical intercept.
              Recall that to do this,
              we will choose one of the two points and plug it into our equation.
              We choose <m>\left(-3,\frac{3}{4}\right)</m>.
